#include <stdio.h>


int main()
{//simple calculator
int a=50,b=10, R;
char choice;
printf("Enter choice");
scanf("%c",&choice);
switch (choice){
case 'a' : R=a+b; printf("R=%d",R); break;
case 's' : R=a-b; printf("R=%d",R); break;
case 'm' : R=a*b; printf("R=%d",R); break;
case 'd' : R=a/b; printf("R=%d",R); break;
default : printf("Wrong choice") ; 
}
return 0;
}

int main()
{ 
    int n,sum=0,r,choice;
    printf("enter any positive number\n");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    int temp=n;
    printf("\nchoice is1: for up to 3 digits only\n");
    printf("\nchoice is2:for 4 digits number\n");
    printf("\nchoice is3: for 5 digits number\n ");
    printf("enter your choice\n");
    scanf("%d",&choice); 
    switch(choice)
    {
        case 1: while(n>0)
                {
                r=n%10;
                sum=sum+r*r*r;
                n=n/10;
                }
                break;        
        case 2: while(n>0)
                { 
                 r=n%10;
                 sum=sum+r*r*r*r;
                 n=n/10;
                 } 
                 break;
        case 3: while(n>0)
                {
                    r=n%10;
                    sum=sum+r*r*r*r*r;
                    n=n/10;
                }
                break;
         deafault:("wrong\n");
                   break;
    }
     if(temp==sum)
     printf("no is armstrong\n"); 
     else
     printf("no is not armstrong\n");
     return (0);
}

07/02/22, 2:22 pm - +91 72329 70452: #include <stdio.h>
 
void swap(int*, int*);
 
int main()
{
   int x, y;
 
   printf("Enter the value of x and y\n");
   scanf("%d%d",&x,&y);
 
   printf("Before Swapping\nx = %d\ny = %d\n", x, y);
 
   swap(&x, &y); 
 
   printf("After Swapping\nx = %d\ny = %d\n", x, y);
 
   return 0;
}
 
void swap(int *a, int *b)
{
   int temp;
 
   temp = *b;
   *b = *a;
   *a = temp;   
}

float percentage(int x,int y, int z);

{

    printf("Enter the marks of 1st subject =");
    scanf("%d",&n1);

    printf("Enter the marks of 2nd subject =");
    scanf("%d",&n2);
    printf("\n");
    printf("Enter the marks of 3rd subject =");
    scanf("%d",&n3);

    printf("\n");

    printf("Percentage of marks = %.2f ",percentage(n1,n2,n3));
}
float average(int x,int y,int z)
{
    float A,B;
    B = x+y+z;
    A = B/3;
    return(A);
}

{
;
    float C,P;
    C = x+y+z;
    P = C/3;
    return(P);
}

void swap(int x,int y)
{
    int c;
    c=x;
    x=y;
    y=c;

}

void swap(int *,int *);
int main()
{
   int a,b;
   printf("Enter two numbers ");
   scanf("%d%d",&a,&b);
   swap(&a,&b);
   printf("a=%d b=%d \n\n",a,b);

void swap(int *x,int *y)
{
    int c;
    c=*x;
    *x=*y;
    *y=c;
}

int sum(int x);
int square(int y);
int main()
{
    int n,a;
    printf("Number of natural numbers sum you want is ");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    sum(n);
    printf("c--(i) Sum of %d natural numbers = %d \n",n,sum(n));
    printf("\n");
    printf("Enter the number ");
    scanf("%d",&a);
    square(a);
    printf("c--(ii) Square of %d natural numbers = %d \n",a,square(a));
    return 0;
}
int sum(int x)
{
    int i,sum=0;
    for(i=1;i<=x;i++)
    {
        sum=sum+i;
    }
    return(sum);
}
int square(int y)
{
    int b;
    b = y * y;
    return(b);
}

_Do you have that Entrepreneurial urge to go to Shark Tank? Do you have a business idea that you want to pitch really bad?_

If yes, then we have got you covered! *Synopsis: The Finance Club of CMS, JMI* presents *"PITCH PERFECT"* - the most exciting Business Plan Competetion of all times!🤩😎
The event will be held in 2 rounds:-

*Round 1:*
Participants will have to take a general awareness Quiz📝 and answer as many correct questions as possible to make it to the second round. 📍This round will be held via Dare2Compete platform.

*Round 2:*
The top scorers from the 1st round will be given a chance to pitch their business idea💡 to our Judging Panel. They will be judged on various parameters and the one idea that will impress our judges the most will be the winner.
📍This round will be conducted via google meet platform.

_🥇Winner and 🥈1st Runner-up will be awarded with E-certificates as well as a recognition post on our social media platform.💫_

*Date🗓️ and Timings🕒*: The first round will be conducted on *24th February, 2022 from 6 p.m. onwards.*
The second round will be held on *26th February, 2022 from 3 p.m. onwards.*

*Guidelines:*
•Participants are welcome in a team of 2-3. Lone wolves are also allowed.
•Inter departmental teams are allowed.
•For round 1, the total time to complete the quiz is 20 minutes. After that, we will not accept any responses.
•In case of a tie, the team/participant with the quicker response time will be selected.
•For round 2, the selected participants should pitch their own business idea. It should not be copied.
•The participants can make either a ppt or a word document or any other form of presentable script that they want to use while pitching their idea.
•10 minutes will be given to each team/participant for presenting their business idea to the judges. Exceeding the time limit will result in negative marking.
• The decision of the judges will be final and shall not be questioned.
•Any form of misconduct will lead to direct disqualification.

So, what are you waiting for! Register now and unleash the hidden entrepreneur within yourself!🔥💥⚡

*Registration link:* https://dare2compete.com/o/OqlH94g?lb=1GYDLzf

11/03/22, 3:55 pm - +91 73196 65434: #include <stdio.h>
 
struct complex
{
   int r, i;
};
 
int main()
{
   struct complex a, b, c;
   int x, y, z;

   printf("Enter the value a and b of the first complex number (a + ib): ");
   scanf("%d%d", &a.r, &a.i);
   printf("Enter the value c and d of the second complex number (c + id): ");
   scanf("%d%d", &b.r, &b.i);
 
   if (b.r != 0 && b.i != 0){

      x = a.r*b.r + a.i*b.i;
      y = a.i*b.r - a.r*b.i;
      z = b.r*b.r + b.i*b.i;

      if (x%z == 0 && y%z == 0)
      {
        if (y/z >= 0)
          printf("Division of the complex numbers = %d + %di", x/z, y/z);
        else
          printf("Division of the complex numbers = %d %di", x/z, y/z);
      }
      else if (x%z == 0 && y%z != 0)
      {
        if (y/z >= 0)
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d + %d/%di", x/z, y, z);
        else
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d %d/%di", x/z, y, z);
      }
      else if (x%z != 0 && y%z == 0)
      {
        if (y/z >= 0)
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d/%d + %di", x, z, y/z);
        else
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d %d/%di", x, z, y/z);
      }
      else
      {
        if (y/z >= 0)
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d/%d + %d/%di",x, z, y, z);
        else
          printf("Division of two complex numbers = %d/%d %d/%di", x, z, y, z);
      }
    }
    else
    {
    printf("Division by 0 + 0i is not allowed.");

    }
 
   return 0;
}

11/03/22, 4:24 pm - +91 72329 70452: #include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>

struct Complex {
    int real, imag;
};

int main ()
{
    int n;
    scanf("%d", &n);
    struct Complex z[n];

    for (int i=0 ; i<n ; i++)
    {
        scanf("%d %d", &z[i].real, &z[i].imag);
    }

    double d[n];
    for( int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        d[i] = sqrt((z[i].real*z[i].real)+(z[i].imag*z[i].imag));
        printf("%f\n", d[i]);
    }

    return 0;
}

typedef struct{
        float a;
        float b;
}Complex;
Complex divide(Complex,Complex);
int main(){
    float a1,b1,a2,b2;
    Complex x,y,z;
    int choice;
    do
    {
        printf("\n\n***MAIN MENU***\n\n");
            puts("1. to find complex nm");
            puts("2. to divide two complex nm");
            puts("3. Exit\n");
            printf("enter choice:");
            scanf(" %d", &choice);
       switch(choice)
       {
           case 1 : {

                      break;
                    }

           case 2 :   {
                        do{
                            printf("Enter first complex number : ");
                            scanf("%f+%fi",&a1,&b1);
                            printf("\nEnter second complex number : ");
                            scanf("%f+%fi",&a2,&b2);
                            if(a2==0.0 && b2 == 0.0)
                                printf("Division by 0 + 0i isn't allowed,  try again\n");
                        }while(a2==0.0 && b2==0.0);
                        x.a = a1; x.b = b1;
                        y.a = a2; y.b = b2;
                        z = divide(x,y);
                        printf("After division: %f+%fi",z.a,z.b);
                        break;
                      }

           case 3 :   {
                        printf("exiting..");
                        exit(1);
                      }
         default :      printf("wrong choice,  enter again\n");
                        break;
       }
     }while(1);
    return 0;
}
Complex divide(Complex x,Complex y){
    Complex z;
    z.a = (x.a*y.a + x.b*y.b)/(y.a*y.a+y.b*y.b);
    z.b = (x.b*y.a - x.a*y.b)/(y.a*y.a + y.b*y.b);
    return z;
}

18/03/22, 7:43 pm - +91 76318 38205: 2.            Program for Matrix Addition, Subtraction and Multiplication in Java

import java.util.Scanner;
class Matrix{
  int A[][];
  int row,col;
  Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
  Matrix(){
  row=0;
  col=0;
  }
  Matrix(int r,int c){
   row=r;
   col=c;
   A=new int[row][col];
   for(int i=0;i<row;i++)
      A[i]=new int[col];
  }
  public void InputMatrix(){
    System.out.println("Enter array elements");
      for(int i=0;i<row;i++)
         for(int j=0;j<col;j++)
            A[i][j]=s.nextInt();
  }
  public Matrix addMatrix(Matrix a){
   Matrix S=new Matrix(this.row,this.col);
   if(this.row!=a.row || this.col!=a.col)
     System.out.println("The dimensions of two matrices must be same");
   else{
         for(int i=0;i<this.row;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<this.col;j++)
               S.A[i][j]=this.A[i][j]+a.A[i][j];
       }
        return S;
  }
  
  public Matrix subMatrix(Matrix a){
   Matrix S=new Matrix(this.row,this.col);
   if(this.row!=a.row || this.col!=a.col)
     System.out.println("The dimensions of two matrices must be same");
   else{
         for(int i=0;i<this.row;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<this.col;j++)
               S.A[i][j]=this.A[i][j]-a.A[i][j];
       }
        return S;
  }
  
  public Matrix mulMatrix(Matrix a){
   Matrix S=new Matrix(this.row,this.col);
   if(this.col!=a.row)
     System.out.println("the columns of first matrix must be equal to rows of second matrix");
   else{
         for(int i=0;i<this.row;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<a.col;j++)
               S.A[i][j]=this.A[i][j]*a.A[i][j];
       }
        return S;
  }
  public void displayMatrix(){
      for(int i=0;i<row;i++){
         for(int j=0;j<col;j++)
             System.out.print("\t"+A[i][j]);
         System.out.print("\n");
     }
  }
}
class SumMatrix{    
  public static void main(String args[]){
         Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
         System.out.print("Enter the number of rows of first matrix");
         int localr=s.nextInt();
         System.out.print("Enter the number of columns of first matrix");
         int localc=s.nextInt();
         Matrix m1=new Matrix(localr,localc);
         m1.InputMatrix();
         m1.displayMatrix();
         System.out.print("Enter the number of rows of second matrix");
         localr=s.nextInt();
         System.out.print("Enter the number of columns of second matrix");
         localc=s.nextInt();
         Matrix m2=new Matrix(localr,localc);
         m2.InputMatrix();
         m2.displayMatrix();
         Matrix m3=m1.addMatrix(m2);
         System.out.println("The sum of two matrices is");
         m3.displayMatrix();
         Matrix m4=m1.subMatrix(m2);
         System.out.println("The difference of two matrices is");
         m4.displayMatrix();
         Matrix m5=m1.mulMatrix(m2);
         System.out.println("The product of two matrices is");
         m5.displayMatrix();
         }
    }
18/03/22, 7:44 pm - +91 76318 38205: .           Program for showing various functionalities of Singly Linked List in Java

import java.util.Scanner;
class LinkedList{
  class Node{
    int data;
    Node next;
    Node(int m){
       data=m;
       next=null;
    }
  }
  static Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
  public Node head=null;
  public Node tail=null;
  public void addNode(){
         int data=s.nextInt();
         Node A=new Node(data);
         if(head==null){
            head=A;
            tail=A;
         }
         else{
             tail.next=A;
             tail=A;
         }
   }
  public void addStart(int data){
         Node p=new Node(data);
         if(head==null){
            head=p;
            tail=p;
         }
         else{
              Node temp=head;
              head=p;
              head.next=temp;
         }
  }
  public void display(){
         Node current= head;
         while(current!=null){
               System.out.println(" "+current.data);
               current=current.next;
         }
  }
  public void addAt(int data,int pos){
         Node B=new Node(data);
         if(head==null){
            head=B;
            tail=B;
         }
         else{
             Node temp,current;
             temp=head;
             current=null;
             for(int i=0;i<pos-1;i++){
                 current=temp;
                 temp=temp.next;
             }
             current.next=B;
             B.next=temp;
         }
  }
  public void DeleteAt(int pos){
         
         if(head==null){
            System.out.println("List is empty");
            return;
         }
         else{
             Node temp=head;
             Node current=null;
             for(int i=0;i<pos-1;i++){
                 current=temp;
                 temp=temp.next;
             }
             if(current!=null){
                current.next=temp.next;
                temp=null;
             }
          }
   }
   public void LinearSearch(int n,int key){
          Node current,temp;
          temp=head;
          current=null;
          for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
              current=temp;
              temp=temp.next;
              if(current.data==key){
                 System.out.println(key+ "is present at position "+(i+1));
                 return;
              }
          }
          if(temp==null){
             System.out.println(key+" is not present in the list");
          }
   }
   public void sortList(){
          Node current=head,index=null;
          int temp;
          if(head==null){
             return;
          }
          else{
              while(current!=null){
                    index=current.next;
                    while(index!=null){
                          if(current.data>index.data){
                             temp=current.data;
                             current.data=index.data;
                             index.data=temp;
                           }
                         index=index.next;
                     }
                   current=current.next;
               }
          }
    } 
   public static void main(String []args){
         LinkedList L1=new LinkedList();
         System.out.println("Enter the number of elements in the list");
         int n=s.nextInt();
         System.out.println("Enter the elements in the list");
         for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
           L1.addNode();
         } 
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add in beginning");
         int start=s.nextInt();
         L1.addStart(start);
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add and at which position");
         int elem=s.nextInt();
         int loc=s.nextInt();                 
         L1.addAt(elem,loc);
         L1.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the position at which you want to delete element");
         int ps=s.nextInt();
         L1.DeleteAt(ps);
         L1.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to search");
         int key=s.nextInt();
         L1.LinearSearch(n,key);
         L1.sortList();
         L1.display();
   }
 }

18/03/22, 7:45 pm - +91 76318 38205: 4.          Program to show the functionalities of Doubly Linked List in java

import java.util.Scanner;
class DoubleLinkedList{
 class Node{
   Node prev;
   int data;
   Node next;
   Node(int m){
       prev=null;
       data=m;
       next=null;
   }
 }
 Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
 public Node head=null;
 public Node tail=null;
 public void addNode(){
        int data=s.nextInt();
        Node A=new Node(data);
        if(head==null){ 
           head=A;
           tail=A;
           head.prev=null;
           tail.next=null;
         }
        else{
           tail.next=A;
           A.prev=tail;
           tail=A;
           tail.next=null;
        }
 }
 public void display(){
        if(head==null){
           System.out.println("List is empty");
           return;
        }
        else{
            Node current=head;
            System.out.println("Nodes of linked list are");
             while(current!=null){
                   System.out.println(current.data+" ");
                   current=current.next;
              }
        }  
 }
 public void addAt(int data,int pos){
         Node B=new Node(data);
         
         if(head==null){ 
           head=B;
           tail=B;
           head.prev=null;
           tail.next=null;
         }
         else{
             Node current,temp;
             current=null;
             temp=head;
             for(int i=1;i<pos;i++){
               current=temp;
               temp=temp.next;
              }
              current.next=B;
              temp.prev=B;
              B.next=temp;
              B.prev=current;
         }
   }
 public void addAtStart(int data){
        Node p=new Node(data);
        if(head==null){
          head=p;
          tail=p;
        }
        else{
             head.prev=p;
             p.next=head;
             p.prev=null;
             head=p;
        }
 }
 public void delete(int pos){
         Node current=head;
         for(int i=1;i<pos;i++){
            current=current.next;
          }
         if(current==head){
            head=current.next;
            }
         else if(current==tail){
                 tail=tail.prev;
               }
         else{
              current.prev.next=current.next;
              current.next.prev=current.prev;
             }
          current=null;
 } 
 public void deleteEnd(){
        if(head==null){
           return;
         }
         else if(head!=tail){
                 tail=tail.prev;
                 tail.next=null;
               }
          else{
               head=tail=null;
          }
   }  
   public void LinearSearch(int n,int key){
          Node current,temp;
          temp=head;
          current=null;
          for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
              current=temp;
              temp=temp.next;
              if(current.data==key){
                 System.out.println(key+ "is present at position "+(i+1));
                 return;
              }
          }
          if(temp==null){
             System.out.println(key+" is not present in the list");
          }
   }
  public void sortList(){
          Node current=head,index=null;
          int temp;
          if(head==null){
             return;
          }
          else{
              while(current!=null){
                    index=current.next;
                    while(index!=null){
                          if(current.data>index.data){
                             temp=current.data;
                             current.data=index.data;
                             index.data=temp;
                           }
                         index=index.next;
                     }
                   current=current.next;
               }
          }
    }   
 public static void main(String []args){
         Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
         DoubleLinkedList L2=new DoubleLinkedList();
         System.out.println("Enter the number of elements in list");
         int n=s.nextInt();
         System.out.println("Enter the elements of linked list");
         for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
             L2.addNode();
         }
         System.out.println("Nodes of linked list are");
         L2.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add and at which position");
         int elem=s.nextInt();
         int pos=s.nextInt();
         L2.addAt(elem,pos);
         L2.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the position at which you want to delete element from the list");
         int del=s.nextInt();
         L2.delete(del);
         L2.display();
         L2.deleteEnd();
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add in start of the list");
         int start=s.nextInt();
         L2.addAtStart(start);
         L2.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to search");
         int ser=s.nextInt();
         L2.LinearSearch(n,ser);
         L2.sortList();
         System.out.println("Sorted list is");
         L2.display();
  }
}
18/03/22, 7:46 pm - +91 76318 38205:    5.                 Program to show the functionailites of Circular Linked List

import java.util.Scanner;
class CircularList{
  class Node{
    int data;
    Node next;
    Node(int m){
        data=m;
        next=null;
    }
  }
  Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
  Node head=null;
  Node tail=null;
  public void insertNode(){
         int data=s.nextInt();
         Node p=new Node(data);
         if(head==null){
            head=p;
            tail=p;
         }
         else{
             tail.next=p;
         }
           tail=p;
           tail.next=head;
  }
  public void display(){
         Node temp=head;
         if(head==null){
            System.out.println("list is empty");
            return;
         }
         else{
            while(temp.next!=head){
                 System.out.println(temp.data);
                 temp=temp.next;
            }
          System.out.println(temp.data);
         }
 }
 public void insertAt(int data,int pos){
        Node p=new Node(data);
         if(head==null){
            head=p;
            tail=p;
         }
         else{
            Node current=null,temp=head;
            for(int i=1;i<pos;i++){
                current=temp;
                temp=temp.next;
             }
         current.next=p;
         p.next=temp; 
        }
 }
 public void addAtEnd(int data){
       Node p=new Node(data);
       Node temp=head;
       while(temp.next!=head){
            temp=temp.next;
        }
       temp.next=p;
       tail=p;
       p.next=head; 
 }
 public void delete(int pos){
        Node temp=head,current=null;
        for(int i=1;i<pos;i++){
           current=temp;
           temp=temp.next;
        }
        current.next=temp.next;
        temp=null;
 }
 public void delEnd(){
        Node temp=head;
        while(temp.next!=tail){
             temp=temp.next;
        }
        tail=temp;
        tail.next=head;
 }
  public void LinearSearch(int key){
          Node current=head;
          int i=1;
          boolean flag=false;
          if(head==null){
             return;
          }
          else{
              do{
                 if(current.data==key){
                    flag=true;
                    break;
                 }
                 current=current.next;
                 i++;
               }while(current!=head);
            if(flag)
                 System.out.println(key +" is found at "+ i);
            else
                 System.out.println(key +" is not found in the list"); 
          }
             
   }
  public void sortList(){
         Node current=head,index=null;
         int temp;
         if(head==null){
           return;
         }
         else{
             do{
                index=current.next;
                while(index!=head){
                      if(current.data>index.data){
                         temp=current.data;
                         current.data=index.data;
                         index.data=temp;
                       }
                    index=index.next;
                 }
               current=current.next;
             }while(current.next!=head);
        }
  }
}
class CircularApp{
  public static void main(String args[]){
      Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
      CircularList L1=new CircularList();
      System.out.println("Enter the number of elements in list");
         int n=s.nextInt();
         System.out.println("Enter the elements of linked list");
         for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
             L1.insertNode();
         } 
      System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add in end");
         int end=s.nextInt();
         L1.addAtEnd(end);
         System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add and at which position");
         int elem=s.nextInt();
         int loc=s.nextInt();                 
         L1.insertAt(elem,loc);
         L1.display();
         System.out.println("Enter the position at which you want to delete element");
         int ps=s.nextInt();
         L1.delete(ps);
         L1.display();
         L1.delEnd();
         L1.sortList();
         System.out.println("Enter the element to be searched");
         int ser=s.nextInt();
         L1.LinearSearch(ser);
         System.out.println("Sorted list is");
         L1.display();
  }
}

Q2. Write a program using Java to compute area of following figures using the concept of function overloading.
(a) Triangle (b) Rectangle (c) Circle 
import java.util.Scanner;
class Area{
   static  int area(int x,int y){
          return(x*y);
   }
   static double area(double x,double y){
           return(0.5*x*y);
   }
   static double area(double r){
          return(3.14*r*r);
   }
 }
 class ShapeArea{
   public static void main(String args[]){
         Scanner s= new Scanner(System.in);
         System.out.println("Enter the sides of rectangle");
         int length=s.nextInt();
         int breadth=s.nextInt();
         System.out.println("The area of rectangle is ");
         System.out.println(Area.area(length,breadth));
         System.out.println("Enter the sides of triangle");
         double base=s.nextDouble();
         double height=s.nextDouble();
         System.out.println("The area of triangle is ");
         System.out.println(Area.area(base,height));
         System.out.println("Enter the radius of circle");
         double rad=s.nextDouble();
         System.out.println("The area of circle is ");
         System.out.println(Area.area(rad));
    }
 }
 Q3. Write a class Worker and derived classes SalaryWorker and DailyWorker. Every worker has a name, address and a salary rate. Write a method computePay(int hours), to compute the weekly pay of every worker. DailyWorker is paid on the basis of the number of days he/she works. The SalaryWorker gets wages for 40 hours a week, no matter how much actual hours he/she has worked. Test this program to calculate the pay of workers. Use the concept of polymorphism.

import java.util.Scanner;
class Worker{
      String Name;
      String Address;
      int SalRate;
      Worker(String Name,String Address,int SalRate){
           this.Name=Name;
           this.Address=Address;
           this.SalRate=SalRate;
      }
     void displayWorker(){
           System.out.println("The details of worker are:");
           
           System.out.println("Name:"+Name);
 
           System.out.println("Address:"+Address);
 
           System.out.println("Rate:"+SalRate);
    }
}     
class DailyWorker extends Worker{
      
       DailyWorker(String Name,String Address,int Rate){
              super(Name,Address,Rate);
              SalRate=Rate;
       }
       void computePay(int hour){
              double days=(double)hour/24;
              if(hour<168){
                         System.out.println("The required salary is:"+(SalRate*days));
               }
              else{
                         
                   System.out.println("Enter valid input");
               }
              
       } 
 }
class SalaryWorker extends Worker{
      
       SalaryWorker(String Name,String Address,int Rate){
              super(Name,Address,Rate);
              SalRate=Rate;
            } 
       void computePay(){
             int hour=40;
             System.out.println("The required pay is:"+(SalRate*hour));
       }
   }
 class Salary{
       public static void main(String args[]){
              String Name; 
              String Address;
              int SalRate;
              int hour;
              Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
              System.out.println("Enter your choice;0 for daily worker and 1 for salary worker");
              int choice=s.nextInt();
              if(choice==0){
                 System.out.println("Enter name:");
                 Name=s.next();
                 System.out.println("Enter address:");                  
                 Address=s.next();
                 System.out.println("Enter rate:");
                 SalRate=s.nextInt();
                 System.out.println("Enter Hours:");
                 hour=s.nextInt();
                 DailyWorker A=new DailyWorker(Name,Address,SalRate);
                 A.displayWorker();
                 A.computePay(hour);
               }
               else if(choice==1){
                 System.out.println("Enter name:");
                 Name=s.next();
                 System.out.println("Enter address:");                  
                 Address=s.next();
                 System.out.println("Enter rate:");
                 SalRate=s.nextInt();
                 SalaryWorker B=new SalaryWorker(Name,Address,SalRate);
                 B.displayWorker();
                 B.computePay();
                }
               else{
                   System.out.println("Enter the valid choice.");
               }
       }
 }

08/05/22, 6:12 pm - Nafisa Jmi: Do anyone know how to insert and delete  multiple elements from an array?
08/05/22, 6:32 pm - +91 76318 38205: 1.                Program to show the functionalities of Array in Java
import java.util.Scanner;
class ArrObj{
  int A[];
  int nElem;
  Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
  public ArrObj(int size){
         A= new int[size];
         nElem=0;
  }
  public void Insert(){
         A[nElem]=s.nextInt();
         nElem++;
  }
  public void InsertAt(int value,int index){
         for(int i=nElem-1;i>=index;i--){
             A[i+1]=A[i];
         }
         A[index]=value;
         nElem++;
  }
  public void Delete(int k){
         for(int i=k;i<nElem;i++){
             A[i]=A[i+1];
         }
         nElem--;
  }
  public void Search(int value){
         for(int i=0;i<nElem;i++){
             if(A[i]==value)
               System.out.println(value+" is present at "+(i+1));
               break;
         }
  }
  public void display(){
         for(int i=0;i<nElem;i++){
             System.out.println(A[i]);
         }
  }
  public void BubbleSort(){
         int n=nElem;
         int temp=0;
         for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
             for(int j=1;j<(n-i);j++){
                 if(A[j-1]>A[j]){
                    temp=A[j-1];
                    A[j-1]=A[j];
                    A[j]=temp;
                 }
              }
          }
   }
   public void binSearch(int key){
          int low=0;
          int high=nElem-1;
          int mid=0;
          while(low<=high){
               mid=(low+high)/2;
               if(key>A[mid])
                 low=mid+1;
               else if(key<A[mid]) 
                 high=mid-1;
               else{
                 System.out.println(key+ "is present in the list at "+mid);
                 break;
               }
           }
           if(low>high)
                 System.out.println(key+ "is nt present in the list");          
    }
}
class ArrayApp{
  public static void main(String args[]){
     Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
     ArrObj a=new ArrObj(20);
     System.out.println("Enter the elements of array");
     for(int i=0;i<5;i++){
         a.Insert();
      }
      System.out.println("Enter the element you want to add and position");
      int elem=s.nextInt();
      int ps=s.nextInt();
      a.InsertAt(elem,ps);
      System.out.println("Displaying all elements of array:");
         a.display();
      System.out.println("Enter the position t which you want to delete");
      int del=s.nextInt();
      a.Delete(del);
      System.out.println("Displaying all elements of array:");
         a.display();
      System.out.println("Enter the element you want to search inlist");
      int ser=s.nextInt();
      a.Search(ser);
      a.BubbleSort();
      System.out.println("Array after bubble sort");
      a.display();
      System.out.println("Enter the element to be searched");
      int bin=s.nextInt();
      a.binSearch(bin);
  }
}

09/05/22, 10:41 am - +91 70862 03433: Following are the rules we should consider while overriding a method properly −

The argument list should be exactly the same as that of the overridden method.
The return type should be the same or a subtype of the return type declared in the original overridden method in the superclass.
The access level cannot be more restrictive than the overridden method's access level. For example: If the superclass method is declared public then the overriding method in the subclass cannot be either private or protected.
Instance methods can be overridden only if they are inherited by the subclass.
A method declared final cannot be overridden.
A method declared static cannot be overridden but can be re-declared.
If a method cannot be inherited, then it cannot be overridden.
A subclass within the same package as the instance's superclass can override any superclass method that is not declared private or final.
A subclass in a different package can only override the non-final methods declared public or protected.
An overriding method can throw any uncheck exceptions, regardless of whether the overridden method throws exceptions or not. However, the overriding method should not throw checked exceptions that are new or broader than the ones declared by the overridden method. The overriding method can throw narrower or fewer exceptions than the overridden method.
Constructors cannot be overridden.

12/05/22, 5:24 pm - Nafisa Jmi: Dear Sir/Madam,
The Ministry of Education’s Innovation Cell and All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) successfully organized four editions of the massive scale nationwide Smart India Hackathon.
Students who have participated in past editions of Smart India Hackathons are cordially invited to the Grand SIH Alumni interaction with Dr. Abhay Jere, CIO, Ministry of Education’s Innovation Cell!
*Date:* 18th May 2022
*Time:* 4.00 PM
*Mode:* Online
Alumni are an institution’s brand ambassadors, carrying their core values of excellence, lifelong learning of inclusiveness, and diversity all around the world.
* The purposes of the alumni association of Smart India Hackathon are:*
• To share your experience with Dr. Abhay Jere, CIO Ministry of Education’s Innovation Cell.
• To introduce a platform to identify the distinguished alumni and share their success stories with the budding innovators.  
• To get support from MIC for your entrepreneurship journey.
Note: Selected success stories will be published on the MIC official website and if approved will also be published in various national/international entrepreneurial/Business magazines and broadcasted on national TV channels.
*Please fill out the google form to confirm your participation. *
https://forms.gle/Z7vqMB4Qephyy7pJ8
*Spread the word around.  Do forward this invite to all your students who have participated in the grand finale of any SIH Edition.*

20/05/22, 3:06 pm - +91 84159 43393: RCA, JMI invites application for free IAS(2022-2023) Coaching  

New Delhi, May 19: The Residential Coaching Academy (RCA), Jamia Millia Islamia (JMI) is inviting applications for Free Coaching (with hostel facility) for the preparation of Civil Services (Preliminary-cum-Main) Examination-2022-2023 from Minority, SC, ST, and Women candidates. The last date for the submission of the online application form is 15th June, 2022.

The university will conduct entrance examination for the selection of candidates on 2nd July, 2022 at ten centres- Delhi, Srinagar, Jammu, Hyderabad, Mumbai, Lucknow, Guwahati, Patna, Bengaluru and Malappuram (Kerala).

Ever since its inception RCA has produced more than 245 Civil Servants and 376 in other Central and State Services including many All India rankers, like Mr. Junaid Ahmad (AIR-3) and Mr. Faiz Aquil  Ahmad (AIR-17).

RCA provides free coaching and training to the underprivileged students with 24x7 library facility and an ecosystem which is one of the best in the country for aspirants of the Civil Services and other competitive examinations.

Detailed information about the eligibility, test centres and other details are available on   https://www.jmi.ac.in and http://jmicoe.in   

Public Relations Office
Jamia Millia Islamia

13/06/22, 6:39 pm - Nafisa Jmi: *TCS*
Google form:https://forms.gle/ftEHzBcnBmUjaTcg7

Eligibility:
• Percentage: Minimum 60% or 6 CGPA throughout academics including the highest qualification,
till the latest semester for which results have been declared. If selected, the offer will be valid only
if the 60% or 6 CGPA criteria is met after completion of the course, at the time of joining.
• Backlogs / Arrears / ATKT: The student should not have more than 1 (one) pending or active
backlog / arrear / ATKT at the time of appearing for the TCS Selection process. If selected, no
pending backlogs / arrears / ATKT will be permitted at the time of joining TCS. All pending backlogs
/ arrears / ATKT should be cleared within the course duration stipulated by the University.
• Gap / Break in Education: It is mandatory to declare academic gaps if any, during the period of
education. Break in education should not be due to extended education (examinations cleared after
the time stipulated by the Board / University). Any break in education should not exceed 24 months
and is permissible only for valid reasons. Relevant document proof, as applicable, will be checked
for gaps in education.
• Course Types: Only Full-Time courses will be considered (Part Time / Correspondence Courses
will not be considered).
• NIOS: Students who have completed their Secondary and / or Senior Secondary course from NIOS
(National Institute of Open Schooling) are also eligible to apply if the other courses are full time.
• Work Experience: Students with prior work experience of up to two years are eligible to apply for
this hiring event.
• Age: A student should be of 18 to 28 years of age to participate in the ‘TCS NQT’.

*NOTE:First fill the form of TCS using the link in the bracket (http://nextstep.tcs.com/campus) and complete all the application procedure. Then fill this form to complete the process.*

Last Date: 13th June by 2 Pm

No Extension will be provided.UPC Jamia Millia Islamia.

Trilogy Hiring: https://forms.gle/hGZCoATyyfm7Pc4ZA
*Deadline : 14th June, till 10pm.*
Role we are hiring for and compensation : Job description attached for your reference and to share with all students

Software Development Engineer (Final year students, passing out in 2023) : Open positions 75+
Compensation: Rs 36.5 Lakhs (Base: Rs 30 LPA + Rs 1L Joining Bonus + Rs 1L TU Graduation bonus + Rs 2.5L Annual Targeted Bonus + Rs 2 L benefits) 
Location: Remote  
Tentative Start Date: 1st August 2023 

Summer Internship Internship profile: SDE Intern( Pre final year students, passing out in 2024) : Open positions 50
Stipend: Rs 1,50,000 + Other benefits 
Location: Remote 
Tentative Start Date: 15th May 2023 

Eligibility Criteria : All Btech / Mtech / Bsc / Msc / BCA / MCA graduates are allowed to apply for the position. 

Note : students from all streams such as Computer science, Information technology, electronics, electrical etc are all eligible. What will make the student successful in our process is mentioned in the attached Student docket for your reference and to share with all students.

Recruitment Process : 
- 120 minutes technical test on an online platform : on 12th June (Will mail test invite to candidats 3 days in advance)
- Shortlisted students from above take a 15 minute CCAT (Cognitive Criteria Aptitude Test)
- Further shortlisted students go through 1-4 rounds of virtual technical interviews [Will start in June last week/ July 1st week]
- Final step is a 15 minute PCCAT (Proctored Cognitive Criteria Aptitude Test)

14/06/22, 1:26 pm - +91 87560 06631: *TCS*
Google form:https://forms.gle/ftEHzBcnBmUjaTcg7

Eligibility:
• Percentage: Minimum 60% or 6 CGPA throughout academics including the highest qualification,
till the latest semester for which results have been declared. If selected, the offer will be valid only
if the 60% or 6 CGPA criteria is met after completion of the course, at the time of joining.
• Backlogs / Arrears / ATKT: The student should not have more than 1 (one) pending or active
backlog / arrear / ATKT at the time of appearing for the TCS Selection process. If selected, no
pending backlogs / arrears / ATKT will be permitted at the time of joining TCS. All pending backlogs
/ arrears / ATKT should be cleared within the course duration stipulated by the University.
• Gap / Break in Education: It is mandatory to declare academic gaps if any, during the period of
education. Break in education should not be due to extended education (examinations cleared after
the time stipulated by the Board / University). Any break in education should not exceed 24 months
and is permissible only for valid reasons. Relevant document proof, as applicable, will be checked
for gaps in education.
• Course Types: Only Full-Time courses will be considered (Part Time / Correspondence Courses
will not be considered).
• NIOS: Students who have completed their Secondary and / or Senior Secondary course from NIOS
(National Institute of Open Schooling) are also eligible to apply if the other courses are full time.
• Work Experience: Students with prior work experience of up to two years are eligible to apply for
this hiring event.
• Age: A student should be of 18 to 28 years of age to participate in the ‘TCS NQT’.

*NOTE:First fill the form of TCS using the link in the bracket (http://nextstep.tcs.com/campus) and complete all the application procedure. Then fill this form to complete the process.*

Last Date: 13th June by 2 Pm

No Extension will be provided.UPC Jamia Millia Islamia.

04/07/22, 1:09 pm - Adiba Khan JMI: Dear Adiba Khan,

Greetings from CSRBOX!!
 
We are extremely delighted to receive nominations from your institution for the IBM Data Analytics Innovation Camp 2022. We are happy to inform you that the nominated teams from your institute will be participating in the upcoming pan-India level Innovation Camp on Data Analytics, which will continue for 6 weeks along with the 16 other colleges participating. We would also like to thank you for responding to us on time and providing us with the necessary data within the given timeline. Since this is a big opportunity for all our partnered colleges, we don't want any of the colleges to miss out on the opportunity for any reason. Hence, due to the delay in submitting the nominations from certain colleges for inevitable reasons, we have decided to shift the Innovation Camp date from July 4th, 2022 to July 11th, 2022. This shifting of dates is to allow us to make the internal preparations to conduct the Innovation Camp efficiently and ensure great learning for all the participants. Hence, we request that you forward the message to your nominated participants, and our team will get in touch with the students this week to circulate the relevant information.

We further request you to nudge the students to remain active during the Innovation camp.

Regards
Team IBM
